We have the following code in [`modelServiceImpl`](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/master/src/vs/editor/common/services/modelServiceImpl.ts#L270):

```typescript
public getCreationOptions(language: string): editorCommon.ITextModelCreationOptions {
	let creationOptions = this._modelCreationOptionsByLanguage[language];
	if (!creationOptions) {
		creationOptions = ModelServiceImpl._readModelOptions(this._configurationService.getConfiguration(null, { overrideIdentifier: language })); // TODO
		this._modelCreationOptionsByLanguage[language] = creationOptions;
	}
	return creationOptions;
}
```

This code currently does not account for folder specific settings, so it seems like when a model is created, potentially wrong options are passed in. The options are:

```typescript
export interface ITextModelCreationOptions {
	tabSize: number;
	insertSpaces: boolean;
	detectIndentation: boolean;
	trimAutoWhitespace: boolean;
	defaultEOL: DefaultEndOfLine;
}
```

This code needs to change in a way that it takes the model resource into account, if it is a file resource. That probably means that we can no longer cache the model creation options, or need a new cache that is multi root aware.

This will enable the `files.eol` setting as a folder setting 👍 

/cc @alexandrudima
